First, we need to calculate the total distance traveled. Since the building has 40 floors and each floor is 5 meters tall, the total distance is:
\[ \text{Total distance} = 40 \text{ floors} \times 5 \text{ meters/floor} = 200 \text{ meters} \]

The elevator accelerates to its maximum speed, then travels at that speed, and finally decelerates to a stop. We can use the kinematic equations to calculate the time taken for each phase.

